SSyynnooppssiiss
       cc [flag . . .] file -lform -locurses [library . . .]

       #include <form.h>

       int  set_field_just(FIELD  *field, int justification); int
       field_just(FIELD *field);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       set_field_just sets the justification for field.  Justifi-
       cation  may  be one of NO_JUSTIFICATION JUSTIFY_RIGHT JUS-
       TIFY_LEFT JUSTIFY_CENTER

       The field justification will be  ignored  if  field  is  a
       dynamic field.

       Field justification will not be allowed for a non-editable
       field.  However, if the field was already justified before
       making it non-editable, it will remain justified.

       field_just  returns  the type of justification assigned to
       field.

 vvaalluuee
       field_just returns one of: NO_JUSTIFICATION  JUSTIFY_RIGHT
       JUSTIFY_LEFT JUSTIFY_CENTER

       set_field_just returns one of the following:
       -----------------------------------------------------------
       E_OK               -   The function returned successfully.
       E_SYSTEM_ERROR     -   System error.
       E_BAD_ARGUMENT     -   An argument is incorrect.
       E_REQUEST_DENIED   -   Justification request denied.

NNoottiicceess
       The  header  file form.h automatically includes the header
       files eti.h and ocurses.h.

